narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: take it if you haven't read these people.
Critical Theory in the Studio should be a mandatory course for any student of art. If you do not take it, your practice will never become a project.
If you're considering this class for any reason at all, take it. Jeffrey Stuker is the most caring and intelligent of teachers.
A great introductionto 20th century critical theory with a wonderful professor. Come prepared to read, write, and talk.
this is quintessential for any art student or creative thinker.
I would highly recommend this class because it seems to be the only one at Yale that provides this very essential content in a way that is suitable for a studio practice.

This class is reading based - every week is based on a reading, some of which are very long and difficult to get through. Each week, a reading response is due, and there is also a midterm essay and final artist statement. If you keep up with the reading, you'll get a lot out of it. If not, there's really no point in taking it.
